overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for response storage, implementing a client-accessible
  dashboard, and securing it with authentication. The assistant began by
  thoroughly evaluating the existing codebase against the provided Statement of
  Work, identifying key missing functionalities such as database schema for
  responses, data retrieval (CSV), and an admin interface with authentication.
  After clarifying the desired authentication complexity (simple password) and
  demographic data fields, a comprehensive plan was developed. The plan detailed
  updates to demographics, creation of a Prisma  model,
  development of API endpoints for saving, listing, and exporting responses, and
  the construction of a simple password-protected admin dashboard. The assistant
  then systematically implemented each part of the plan, including necessary
  code modifications and new file creations, successfully delivering a
  functional database, authentication system, and admin dashboard with CSV
  export capabilities.
